A cool retro-industrial space, but on a first visit, the food itself was sort of meh.  I was very excited to try something from the motherland, eh? And I love burgers, and also off-beat concepts. But...the poutine was just so-so. "Okay" fries and cheese curds that were too old to squeak (curds less than a day old should be "squeaky" when you bite into them).  The burger (served well-done only) is a burst of acceptable-but-mediocre. Well-done makes for a patty that takes talent to make flavorful (it wasn't). The bread could be a highlight in this part of Baltimore that's long been a center of commercial bakeries, but it was just "fine". The smoked bacon is cooked so long it's lost all bacony-ness and tastes merely of smoke.  For drunk-food? Totally acceptable. If you're local to this location, it's outside of the bustle and parking pain of the waterfront districts. For food you want to seek out for the food itself? Not so much.
